    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "name": "Tidal volume (Vt)",
        "category": "Ventilation",
        "subcategory": "Ventilation parameters",
        "shortDescription": "Tidal volume (Vt) — gas volume per breath, in mL (inspired/expired, spontaneous/mandatory, setting). Per-kg form is separate.",
        "longDescription": "## Definition & Clinical Context\n\nTidal volume (Vt) is the volume of gas moved in or out of the lungs in a single breath. In ventilated patients it is set and/or measured by the ventilator and is central to lung-protective ventilation (commonly targeted by predicted body weight). In source data it is a single numeric value per patient-timestamp. It is recorded in intensive care and anaesthesia for ventilated patients. This set captures tidal volume as an absolute volume, reported in millilitres (mL); some sources use litres (L), which is inter-convertible (1 L = 1000 mL). Tidal volume normalised to body weight (mL/kg) is a different, non-inter-convertible measurement kept in a separate set — see Mapping Notes.\n\n## Included Concepts\n\nThe set lists the SNOMED and LOINC tidal-volume concepts reported as an absolute volume (mL), grouped by what they qualify. Several LOINC concepts come in variants corrected or uncorrected for compressible gas volume in the circuit; both are included.\n\n### Generic / total (default)\n\n- *4029625 / 13621006 — Tidal volume (SNOMED)*\n- *21490854 / 76222-9 — Tidal volume Ventilator --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3004732 / 20118-6 — Tidal volume.spontaneous+mechanical --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3017707 / 20121-0 — Tidal volume.spontaneous+mechanical uncorrected for compressible gas volume --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n- *3007828 / 20119-4 — Tidal volume.spontaneous+mechanical corrected for compressible gas volume --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n### Inspired\n\n- *44782826 / 698823007 — Inspiratory tidal volume (SNOMED)*\n- *36303816 / 76221-1 — Tidal volume.inspired (LOINC)*\n- *3033780 / 20110-3 — Tidal volume inspired spontaneous+mechanical --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3016166 / 20109-5 — Tidal volume inspired spontaneous+mechanical Measured --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3021470 / 20111-1 — Tidal volume inspired spontaneous+mechanical corrected for compressible gas volume --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n### Expired\n\n- *44782827 / 698824001 — Expiratory tidal volume (SNOMED)*\n- *21490752 / 75958-9 — Tidal volume expired Respiratory system airway (LOINC)*\n- *21490789 / 76007-4 — Tidal volume expired Respiratory system airway --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3015016 / 20107-9 — Tidal volume expired spontaneous+mechanical Respiratory system airway --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3009097 / 20108-7 — Tidal volume expired spontaneous+mechanical corrected for compressible gas volume --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3011767 / 20106-1 — Tidal volume expired spontaneous corrected for compressible gas volume Respiratory system airway --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n### Spontaneous\n\n- *4108448 / 250816009 — Spontaneous tidal volume (SNOMED)*\n- *3017594 / 20116-0 — Tidal volume.spontaneous --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n### Mandatory\n\n- *4353946 / 250817000 — Mandatory tidal volume (SNOMED)*\n\n### Sigh\n\n- *3008805 / 20114-5 — Tidal volume sigh spontaneous+mechanical --on ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n### Setting\n\n- *3012410 / 20112-9 — Tidal volume setting Ventilator (LOINC)*\n- *3020572 / 20105-3 — Tidal volume expired spontaneous uncorrected for compressible gas volume setting Ventilator (LOINC)*\n\n**Note on units**: reported in **mL** (`8587 / mL — milliliter`, UCUM), the recommended unit, with a registered mL↔L conversion (1 L = 1000 mL).\n\n## Mapping Notes\n\n- **Default concept** when the source records a tidal volume without qualification: *4029625 / 13621006 — Tidal volume*.\n- **Expired is the usual measured value**: ventilators typically report expired tidal volume; map to an expired concept when specified, otherwise use the generic concept.\n- **Setting vs measured**, **inspired vs expired**, **spontaneous vs mandatory**: map to the specific concept only when the source documents that distinction; otherwise use the generic concept.\n- **Compressible-gas correction**: some LOINC concepts distinguish values corrected vs uncorrected for gas compressed in the circuit; map to the matching variant if the source states it, else use the plain concept.\n- **Per body weight is separate**: tidal volume normalised to body weight (mL/kg) belongs to the separate Tidal volume per body weight concept set — mL and mL/kg are not inter-convertible without the patient's weight.\n- Convert a value in L to mL (×1000) before mapping.\n"
      },
